Update Sets (ServiceNow)
🔹 What are Update Sets?

Update Sets in ServiceNow are used to capture, track, and move configuration changes from one instance to another (for example: Development → Test → Production).

They help manage application customization and deployment across environments.

🔹 Features
Captures configuration changes
Moves customizations between instances
Tracks development work
Supports application deployment
Maintains change history
🔹 What Update Sets Capture

✅ Forms and fields changes
✅ Business Rules
✅ Client Scripts
✅ UI Policies
✅ UI Actions
✅ Workflows
✅ Application configuration

🔹 What Update Sets Do NOT Capture

❌ User data / records
❌ Attachments
❌ Reports data
❌ System logs
❌ Scheduled job execution history

🔹 Components
1. Current Update Set

Active update set where changes are stored.

2. Default Update Set

System-generated update set available by default.

3. Retrieved Update Set

Imported update set from another instance.

4. Completed Update Set

Finalized update set ready for migration.

🔹 Update Set Process

Create Update Set
↓
Make Configuration Changes
↓
Mark as Complete
↓
Export / Retrieve
↓
Preview Update Set
↓
Commit to Target Instance

🔹 Benefits
Easy migration of customizations
Supports controlled deployment
Prevents manual recreation
Maintains consistency across environments
🔹 Example

Developer creates a Business Rule and UI Policy in Development → Captured in Update Set → Moved to Test → Deployed to Production.
